Deep within the Imperial Mountain, the small diamond beetle digs endlessly through even the hardest stone and white jade.
Although one water buffalo can tell itself apart from another, a watching predator cannot do so.
Animals know one another as friend or foe.
Once a true predator catches a scent, she never lets it go.
A hawk can dive through a cloud of thrushes and kill only one.
The overprotective bird pecks anything that comes near her nest or her food.